title: Rail
description:
The SkyTrain connects the airport terminal with Düsseldorf Flughafen railway station, where over 350 trains from S-Bahns (urban trains) to ICEs (intercity express trains), stop at Düsseldorf Airport train station everyday.
Skytrain makes an intermediate stop at Car Park 4 (also accessible from Car Park 5).
The SkyTrain operates daily from 03:45 to 00:45 (also longer if necessary) every 3.5 - 7 minutes between the terminal and main-line station.
More information about trains

title: Rail
description:
The Düsseldorf Airport terminal train station is located below terminal C and can be reached via a moving walkway from the arrivals area. From here, you can travel on the S11 to Bergisch Gladbach via Düsseldorf central station.
More information about trains

title: Taxis and Public Transportation
description:
Taxis
Certified Airport Taxis are identified by an Airport Taxi sticker.
More information about taxis

Local Bus Service
The bus station is located in front of the main Arrivals hall.
Bus 721 to/from Tannenhof/Gothaer Weg via Düsseldorf main railway station
Bus 760 to/from Ratingen and Düsseldorf-Wittlaer-Bockum, Rosspfad
Bus SB51 to/from Kaarst-Rathaus via Düsseldorf-Nordfriedhof, Meerbusch
Bus 896 Düsseldorf-Flughafen Terminals A/B/C shuttle to Düsseldorf-Messe (trade fair centre) (not all trade fairs)

More information about buses
